DE  Decarboxylation/antiport proton-motive cycle: lysine-cadaverine
TP  SYSTEM
AU  Haft DH
TH  0
RN  [1]
RM  16877381
RT  Identification of the cadaverine recognition site on the
RT  cadaverine-lysine antiporter CadB.
RA  Soksawatmaekhin W, Uemura T, Fukiwake N, Kashiwagi K, Igarashi K;
RL  J Biol Chem. 2006;281:29213-29220.
CC  The decarboxylation of lysine to cadaverine consumes a proton. Exchange
CC  of lysine for cadaverine by an antiporter completes a cycle that
CC  effectively removes a cytosolic proton. Decarboxylation/antiporter
CC  systems for this and other (e.g. aspartate-alanine) substrate pairs can
CC  provide protection against acidic pH.
